title: For Sale/Trade:  [TRADES ADDED] 1939 Walther PPK .32ACP/7.65mm w/2 magazines & holster
postcontent: Up for sale is a 1939 made, Walther PPK in the original .32ACP/7.65 made in Zella-Mehlis. It has no import marks, just the usual Waffenfabrik Walther Zella Mehlis (Thür) Walther's Patent Cal 7,65 m/m Mod. PPk. Serial# is 248409K, indicating it was made at the end of 1939, right before they started being Nazi stamped. It is in great condition. Mechanically perfect, and shoots great (I put approx 100 rounds through it). Finish is at least 95%, with just some carry wear on the left side that is shown in the pictures. This was most likely carried by a German soldier/Police officer before it was brought back to the US. Has a hairline crack around the grip screw (99% of Bakelite grip equipped PPK's do).It comes with two original 7.65 Walther marked magazines, one shows wear and has clearly been used a bit, the other one is in fantastic shape and doesn't look like it's been used at all. Also comes with a wartime leather DRGM Akah stamped that was (so I've been told) brought back with the gun by the same soldier. This holster has clearly been well used, and was actually on fire at some point in Germany (Flap missing, rear of the holster shows burn marks). I'm asking $1000 for everything These usually go for well over that (Cheapest one on Gunbroker right now is $1200+, cheapest on Armslist is $700 for one with about 10% finish left and $800 for one with about 60% finish left) and that's just with one mag, and no holster (or 70% holster? lol) so I believe $1000 is MORE than fair for this gorgeous old gun, two mags, and the holster.Willing to consider all FAIR trade offers for firearms.
